---
const title = "THE SHOP // PERSONAL_LAB";
---
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;700&display=swap" rel="stylesheet">
    <style>
        body { background: #0a0a0a; color: #a0a0a0; font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; padding: 40px; }
        header { border-bottom: 1px solid #333; padding-bottom: 20px; margin-bottom: 40px; }
        h1 { color: #00ff41; font-size: 1.2rem; }
        .grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr)); gap: 20px; }
        .card { border: 1px solid #222; padding: 20px; background: #111; }
        .card h3 { color: #fff; margin-top: 0; font-size: 0.9rem; border-bottom: 1px solid #222; padding-bottom: 10px; }
        .tag { font-size: 0.6rem; color: #00ff41; border: 1px solid #00ff41; padding: 2px 5px; margin-right: 5px; }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <header>
        <h1>[ {title} ]</h1>
        <a href="/" style="color: #666; text-decoration: none; font-size: 0.7rem;">&lt; RETURN_TO_ROOT</a>
    </header>
    <div class="grid">
        <div class="card">
            <h3>3D_PRINTING_LOGS</h3>
            <p>Functional prints for the woodshop. Currently focusing on PETG-CF and Nylon-CF for high-stress components.</p>
            <span class="tag">BAMBU_A1_MINI</span><span class="tag">H2D</span>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
            <h3>WOODWORKING_GALLERY</h3>
            <p>1x4 furniture hobbyist. Custom Lego displays for the boys and shop organization.</p>
            <span class="tag">FURNITURE</span><span class="tag">LEGOS</span>
        </div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
